        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         <em>
          <strong>
           I have a confession to make: I can't stop investing in art.
          </strong>
          It started small. I invested in Basquiat\xe2\x80\x99s
         </em>
         Loin
         <em>
          in 2020. And I got hooked.
         </em>
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         <em>
          Today, there are 10 paintings in the Not Boring portfolio. I recently added the Picasso masterpiece from the striking image above. Instead of breaking my addiction, my New Year's resolution is to double down and buy as much art as possible, because
          <strong>
           I believe that art is a key part of a balanced portfolio
          </strong>
          .
          <strong>
           Here's why:
          </strong>
         </em>
        </p>
        <ul style="margin-top: 0;">
         <li style="margin-bottom: 3.75px; margin-left: 7.5px; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 3.75px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">
           <em>
            UBS reports that two-thirds of high-net-worth collectors buy art for an expected ROI
           </em>
          </p>
         </li>
         <li style="margin-bottom: 3.75px; margin-left: 7.5px; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 3.75px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">
           <em>
            Real assets like art appreciate well during periods of high inflation
           </em>
          </p>
         </li>
         <li style="margin-bottom: 3.75px; margin-left: 7.5px; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 3.75px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">
           <em>
            Blue-chip Art prices outpaced the S&amp;P 500 from 1995 to 2021, according to Citi
           </em>
          </p>
         </li>
        </ul>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         <em>
          But even though I\xe2\x80\x99m bullish, I didn't throw down $100 million at auction. I just used
