        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         In
         <em>
          Complexity
         </em>
         , Waldrop explained Arthur\xe2\x80\x99s economic agents further: \xe2\x80\x9cThey would be no more governed by mathematical formulas than human beings are. As a practical matter, of course, they would have to be far simpler than real human beings\xe2\x80\xa6\xe2\x80\x9d
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
